subSubSection.paragraph:
Type locality . D Site (“ BMR Locality 103D” in Rich, 1979 ), Riversleigh World Heritage Area, Lawn Hill National Park, northwestern Queensland , Australia . Based on biostratigraphic and biocorrelative analyses, D Site forms part of Riversleigh’s “Faunal Zone A”, and as such is interpreted to be Late Oligocene in age (
Archer et al ., 1997
; Arena, 2004 ;
Travouillon et al ., 2006
).

